e":"sriharsha","key":"sriharsha","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Sriharsha Chintalapani","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"created":"2015-01-20T16:22:00.959+0000","updated":"2015-01-20T16:22:00.959+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12736453/comment/14283971","id":"14283971","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=longtimer","name":"longtimer","key":"longtimer","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Jason Kania","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Toronto"},"body":"I think it would help to link from the error to the longer form error and to include text indicating the log file in which the error can also be seen. That is what would have helped me at the time.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=longtimer","name":"longtimer","key":"longtimer","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Jason Kania","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Toronto"},"created":"2015-01-20T16:22:47.442+0000","updated":"2015-01-20T16:22:47.442+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12736453/comment/14283995","id":"14283995","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=dagit","name":"dagit","key":"dagit","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=dagit&avatarId=25742","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=dagit&avatarId=25742","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=dagit&avatarId=25742","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=dagit&avatarId=25742"},"displayName":"Derek Dagit","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Chicago"},"body":"That could be tricky.  The storm worker code would need to know the byte-offset into the log at which the error occurred and report that as part of the error, and I'm not sure we would want the worker to know such details of the logging system.\n\nRecently we started testing a change to storm that allows us to search the most recent, active worker logs for a fixed string.  Once we find the opportunity to submit it to apache/storm, we could then add a link to perform a search on the corresponding worker log for that sub-string that we see now.  This way the storm worker code does not have to know where its log messages are going or know anything about file offsets.\n\nWe could click this new link next to the cut-off error text and we would be able to see any instances in the real worker log file with that error snippet.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=dagit","name":"dagit","key":"dagit","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=dagit&avatarId=25742","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=dagit&avatarId=25742","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=dagit&avatarId=25742","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=dagit&avatarId=25742"},"displayName":"Derek Dagit","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Chicago"},"created":"2015-01-20T16:45:24.031+0000","updated":"2015-01-20T16:45:24.031+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12736453/comment/14284050","id":"14284050","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=longtimer","name":"longtimer","key":"longtimer","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Jason Kania","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Toronto"},"body":"Such a solution would have helped me significantly.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=longtimer","name":"longtimer","key":"longtimer","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Jason Kania","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Toronto"},"created":"2015-01-20T17:15:37.479+0000","updated":"2015-01-20T17:15:37.479+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12736453/comment/14284556","id":"14284556","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rekhajoshm","name":"rekhajoshm","key":"rekhajoshm","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/use